If DHR contacts you please get an attorney before you go see them. BEFORE YOU TALK TO DHR, PLEASE HAVE AN ATTORNEY.

If you do cave and sign it, they might tell you its only 45 days and its all over, but thats a LIE. Its 45 days for the case worker on the Safety Plan to create a petition against you that an Attorney has and presents to a judge against you. There is actually 60 days till they decide to drop it or make charges. They may say they will get you a free attorney, but get your own before they can cause any trouble to begin with. Also the attorney that is free is for your children so that DHR can make sure the children are safe. Safe against who, well that is you of course. You are getting a free attorney to prosecute you. Thanks DHR.

But wait there is more. During your so called Safety Plan they are going to want you to come in after 30 days and sign a ISP. That is an Individualized Service Plan. But you are on a Safety Plan already, so why do you need a new plan.  Well its so DHR can threaten you again. We were told they could have Foster Care there that day to take the kids. So you still don't have an Attorney and they scare you again into signing a new plan.

Well its 2 months into it now. DHR will make you take Classes. Any class they can to prolong the case and assure they are making more money. The longer the case is open, the more cases they can show they have and get more money from the state. You will have attended another ISP and most likely through out all of this DHR will have told you very little and you half of what they told you is a Lie. They might say they were super busy and sorry I sent you the wrong document. Sorry I never said that time, and change you visitation times. Sorry I meant you both need to take these classes now, but you said only I had to.

Well by now, you have finished your Classes and after trying really hard to have DHR get back with you, so your kids can come home, you finally get your kids back. Its been 3 to 4 months now.  Things are getting better.

But wait there is more. DHR can still investigate you another 90 days. Or so I was told. Maybe it is 90 days until she says my carpet is to dirty and adds on another 90 days. Who knows but they will continue to investigate you and your child's school for months, to a year, or even years.

Hopefully if you get Attorney before you ever speak with DHR. Your attorney will tell you what to NOT SAY and what to NOT DO so that DHR doesn't have any AMMO against you.  Get an Attorney to go with you to meet DHR. Do Not Go Alone like me and get abused by DHR. I am still paying for it.

name: Sarah Capps
text: In the big picture our time with DHR as foster parents has been fairly positive. They give you a license, after they have been through your life, your home your extended family, and with recommendations from friends and co-workers paid babysitting and other fees to go to classes, this license that says you are clear to be foster parents, teaming up and working with DHR working together for the good of the children. This happened about 10 years ago in Madison County, DHR in Madison county stood by us when the CAJA worker and birth grand parents tried to press charges against us. They stood by us as we had to take our foster kids to CAC to talk about serious abuse that happened BEFORE they came to live with us. All documented in court, the  CAC and  DHR in Madison County.  We got a copy of all this when we adopted the kids. fast forward to 4 years ago we were able to do a private placement adoption, after we moved to Limestone County and were not longer licensed foster parents. Things went smoothly. This was a second chance adoption. this child had been in and out of foster care, and was adopted, but  it just didn't work out. Fast forward to about a year ago. We were asked to renew our license to help out some people who were loosing their kids to foster care. Once again the DHR social workers were good, and took time to make sure all was well and safe in our back ground and current home. These beautiful children were placed in our home. One of these kids started talking about a lot of serious abuse that happened BEFORE they came to live with us. My own adopted kids were still in therapy because of their abuse, so I started to make sure these kids were getting the help they needed to get the support they needed to understand boundaries, and what is safe and what isn't ok, and that NONE of it is their fault. Well as life opened up, and some things happened, DHR in Limestone county didn't believe us, they didn't even try to look into what happened in Madison County. They kept saying they would talk to me and my husband. NEVER happened. but all of a sudden, these beautiful children are removed from our home. one of my older sons was removed from our home, and labeled as a child sex abuser. His name is on the central registry.  No due process, just bam and a letter so brutal, and labled as fact as if and investigation really did happen. Something that happens and it's just so unreal, you have a hard time believing this is happening in America, where you are innocent until proven guilty. (btw you only are allowed any type of due process if you are a child care professional so some sort foster parents and their families aren't considered professional)  We are now being stabbed in the back, in the most cannibalistic way.  DHR comes into every aspect of your life and family and says "Here take these broken abused kids, oh they have problems, too bad" Not only did they not help, they totally threw us under the bus. My younger son still wakes up a year later hoping to wake up to a day of fun with his foster brother then realizes that bed on the other side of the room is empy. DHR Limestone county took our broken family and family we were trying to heal, build and make lasting relationships with. and just threw us under the bus, and didn't even look back. NO DUE PROCESS!  What hurts the most I loved being a foster parent. I LOVED these kids, we as a family all worked so hard together to support them and help each other. Yes I would do it all again, and yes I want to do it again if we ever get this mess cleaned up and find some kind of due process for our son. I don't want to turn away any foster parent but be prepared, document EVERYTHING.

They assisted and trained my father with taking his blood sugar readings and insulin injections.  They offer a variety of services and you can pick the service(s) that best suits your needs.  Their prices are very reasonable.  If you need a senior care professional for your elderly parent, "Your Choice Senior Care" is the first call you should make.

name: Richard Davidson
text:
I highly recommend Your Choice Senior Care for anyone needed help caring for somebody. We’ve relied on Your Choice for well over a year to help care for my 97 year old mother. The company’s owners/managers are conscientious, hard-working, and responsive to our concerns.

One caveat: the quality of individual caregivers varies considerably, from excellent too awful. The best are more than caregivers; they are friends, both with my mom and my wife and myself. A rare few were bad enough I ordered them to leave and not return. The owners and managers are careful with who they hire, and pass on our instructions for what is expected from the caregivers, but they cannot monitor everything happening in your home.  In the end, it is up to you to determine which caregivers meets your needs and which have to go.

That said, anytime there has been problem with a caregiver—no matter the time, day or night—the owners/managers have acted *immediately* to correct the problem, including personally caring for my mom until a replacement caregiver was found.  They strive to provide excellent care to the elderly, and their efforts have made it possible for my mom to continue living with us long after she surpassed our ability to care for her by ourselves.

This is the most poorly run establishment ever. It is not a "charity," it is a federally contracted facility. They use their Non-Profit Status as a way to avoid paying income taxes on all the money they get from both you and the government.
If you have ever been to any county or state work release you'll know exactly what to expect. All they are worried about is getting you in the door, you finding a job, and you paying 25% of your gross weekly to them.
If you are genuinely interested in any form of help I would suggest that you go out and get it on your own.There is one particular agency in town that is willing to offer help, The Family Guidance Center, and they will not allow you to go there.
If you are coming from Federal Prison, I would suggest you get insurance. Should you not do that, expect typical Federal Healthcare.
If you are trying to remain sober I would figure out a way to get out of there ASAP. You may be able to pull off a meeting here and there, but you are basically allowed one. If you want to get high, just go to the bathroom.
Not all of the apples there, aka staff, are bad. Some would actually like to see you progress in life. For the rest the job is nothing but a paycheck. The rules vary from shift to shift, person to person, etc. There is no leadership whatsoever, every most all employees think they are the boss.
They forget that the only reason they have a job is because of us.if you are going, bring a pen. Take my advice, just remember that you can write them up just like when you were behind the fence. Also you can call the Dismas Corporate Office and speak to the Regional Supervisor, or you can call the Resident Re-entry Manager at Maxwell.
The choice is up to you!

Sincerely,
SADIII

Ps. I gave it one star because I had to, so I could post.
